import Mathlib
open Subgroup

/-- If H ⊲ G, K ⊲ G, and H ≤ K then (K/H) ⊲ (G/H) and (G/H)/(K/H) ≅ G/K. -/
lemma quotient_normalizer_le_normalizer_tac_1465 (H : Subgroup G) (K : Subgroup G) (hH : H.Normal) (hK : K.Normal) (h : H ≤ K) : (K ⧸ H).Normal ∧ (G ⧸ H) ⧸ (K ⧸ H) ≃* G ⧸ K := by sorry

import Mathlib
universe u

variable {G : Type u} [Group G]
variable (H K : Subgroup G)
variable (hH : H ⊲ G) (hK : K ⊲ G) (h : H ≤ K)

/-- If H ≤ K with H and K normal in G, then (K/H) is normal in (G/H) and
  there is a canonical isomorphism ((G/H)/(K/H)) ≃ G/K. -/
lemma quotient_normal_and_iso :
  ((K ⧸ H) ⊲ (G ⧸ H)) ∧ (((G ⧸ H) ⧸ (K ⧸ H)) ≃* (G ⧸ K)) := by
  sorry
